Control mixer for the differentially driven balancing robot.

Combines the total drive torque from the balance/position controller with the
differential torque from the yaw controller into individual wheel torque
commands. The total drive torque is preserved (`left + right = drive`), and
the differential component (`left - right = yaw_torque`) produces a yaw
moment. Since positive wheel torque drives the robot toward negative x, a
positive differential torque on the left wheel pushes the left side backward,
turning the robot counterclockwise seen from above (positive yaw).

